description:
Locations: secretx-pkcs11/src/lib.rs:709-715 and 732-735 — both in integration test setup.

Current code:
    let lib = match std::env::var("PKCS11_LIB") {
        Ok(v) => v,
        Err(_) => {
            eprintln!("PKCS11_LIB not set; skipping integration test");
            return;
        }
    };

Idiomatic equivalent (let-else, stable since 1.65, well below MSRV 1.75):
    let Ok(lib) = std::env::var("PKCS11_LIB") else {
        eprintln!("PKCS11_LIB not set; skipping integration test");
        return;
    };

Why it matters: let-else expresses "extract the happy-path value or diverge" in one line. The match form requires the reader to confirm the Ok arm just yields v with no transformation — extra cognitive load for a pattern that has a dedicated language construct.

Both clippy::manual_let_else and clippy::single_match_else flag this in pedantic mode.
